import java.util.HashSet;
import java.util.Set;
import java.util.Vector;

public Vector<Integer> paintingPlan(int[][] paint) {
    Vector<Integer> worklog = new Vector<>(paint.length);
    Set<Integer> painted = new HashSet<>();

    for (int i = 0; i < paint.length; i++) {
        int start = paint[i][0];
        int end = paint[i][1];
        int day_work = 0;

        for (int j = start; j < end; j++) {
            if (!painted.contains(j)) {
                painted.add(j);
                day_work++;
            }
        }

        worklog.add(day_work);
    }

    return worklog;
}
```

    The algorithm follows these steps:
1. Create an array or vector `worklog` which will store the new painted areas on each day, and set all the initial values to 0.
2. Create a set `painted` which will store the areas (integer points) that have already been painted.
3. Iterate through the given `paint` array, for each day:
   1. Extract the start and end points of the painting area.
   2. Iterate through the points between the start and end.
   3. If the point is not in the `painted` set, add it to the set and increment the counter for the current day in the `worklog` array.
4. Return the `worklog` array.
